  "prompt": "Why is the Duronto train green?",
  "response": "The Duronto Express trains in India are characterized by their distinctive green color, which is part of their branding. The green color is often associated with speed and efficiency, reflecting the Duronto trains' purpose of providing a fast and non-stop service between major cities. \n\nThe choice of color can also be linked to environmental concerns, as green is commonly associated with nature and sustainability. Additionally, the green livery helps to differentiate these trains from others in the Indian Railways fleet, making them easily identifiable to passengers.\n\nOverall, the green color represents a combination of aesthetic branding, operational attributes, and environmental considerations.",
